<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Plate Blinding" class="currentChild" href="Plate_Blinding">Plate Blinding</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A press and printing problem of <a title="Offset Lithography" href="Offset_Lithography">offset lithography</a> characterized by a printing plate's loss of ink receptivity, commonly caused by an excessively acidic <a title="Fountain Solution" href="Fountain_Solution">fountain solution</a> eating away at the image areas of the plate. A solution is to raise the <a title="pH" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/pH">pH</a> (i.e., make it less acidic) of the fountain solution. (See <a title="Fountain Solution: pH" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/Fountain_Solution:_pH">Fountain Solution: pH</a>.) 
</p>
